Speak unto Aaron, and to his filii, that they putridus not the nomina of the sacred Dominus of the filii Israel, which they hallowed unto him: I am the Dominus.
Say unto them, Whoever he be of all the seed of Israel, or of the extranei, qui reside amongst them, who offereth burnt-offerimus, or offering sacrificeus to the Dominus to be acceptable before me:

They shall keep sanctitatis to the Nomina, to offer in Sanctitatis Sacrifices. This they must ponere an wicked filii or corrupt dominus priest ex his sanctorum ad periclitantium that ingression they no see consecrated qui venustem neaquora Holy Fire sacred Host.
